24. There were three fora at Rome—(1) forum Romanorum, (2) forum Caesaris, (3) forum Augusti3 and there were three theatres, called respectively the theatre of (1) Pompey, (2) Marcellus, and (3) Statilius.

terna: the distributive is here perhaps used by poetic license for tria, the cardinal number. Distributives are used instead of cardinal numbers with nouns which have no singular. Here, perhaps, a distributive is used because each forum has its place taken by a theatre. Cf. El. viii„ 1. 34.
